{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 12:17:50.154679", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary\\n- Overall state: Partial outage affecting the 10.2.1.0/24 access domain. The 10.1.1.0/24 domain and the server farm are healthy.\\n- Primary anomaly: Host in 10.2.1.0/24 lacks an IP address (DHCP failure) and that distribution area has no reachability to the server farm (10.200.0.0/24).\\n- Root cause: OSPF area mismatch on router_core_2 isolates area 1 behind router_core_2 from the OSPF backbone (area 0), preventing inter-area routing and DHCP relay to the central server.\\n\\nFindings and Evidence\\n\\n1) Host and end-to-end reachability\\n- host_1_1_1_1 (10.1.1.10/24 via DHCP):\\n  - IP config: 10.1.1.10/24, default via 10.1.1.1. resolv.conf nameserver 10.200.0.2.\\n  - Reachability: Pings to dns_server (10.200.0.2) and web_server_3 (10.200.0.6) succeed. get_reachability shows 0% loss and low RTTs.\\n  - Web access: curl http://web99.local completes with total ~1.1–1.3s; curl http://web0.local and http://10.200.0.3 complete with total ~2.0–2.2s. DNS resolution times are small, indicating DNS is functioning.\\n\\n- host_2_1_1_1:\\n  - No IP address on eth0 (no inet line in ip addr). No routes present.\\n  - Pings from this host to dns_server/load_balancer fail immediately with “Network is unreachable.”\\n  - resolv.conf lists nameserver 10.200.0.2, but without an IP configuration the host cannot use it.\\n  - Conclusion: DHCP failed on this access domain.\\n\\n2) OSPF adjacencies and routing\\n- OSPF neighbors:\\n  - router_core_1: Neighbors with router_core_3 and router_dist_1_1 (Full).\\n  - router_core_3: Neighbors with router_core_1 and server_access_router (Full).\\n  - server_access_router: Neighbor with router_core_3 (Full).\\n  - router_dist_1_1: Neighbor with router_core_1 (Full).\\n  - router_dist_2_1: Neighbor with router_core_2 (Full).\\n  - router_core_2: Only neighbor shown is router_dist_2_1. No neighbor with router_core_1 or router_core_3.\\n  - Conclusion: router_core_2 is not peering with the other cores; its core-facing links are not in the same area as the rest of the backbone.\\n\\n- OSPF configurations:\\n  - router_core_1: core links 172.16.0.0/31 and 172.16.0.2/31 in area 0; dist1 link 172.16.0.6/31 in area 1.\\n  - router_core_3: core links 172.16.0.2/31, 172.16.0.4/31 and server link 172.16.0.10/31 all in area 0.\\n  - server_access_router: 10.200.0.0/24 and 172.16.0.10/31 in area 0.\\n  - router_dist_1_1: 10.1.1.0/24 and 172.16.0.6/31 in area 1.\\n  - router_dist_2_1: 10.2.1.0/24 and 172.16.0.8/31 in area 1.\\n  - router_core_2: 172.16.0.0/31 and 172.16.0.4/31 configured in area 66, and 172.16.0.8/31 in area 1.\\n  - Conclusion: router_core_2 has its core-facing links in area 66 instead of area 0, causing an area mismatch with router_core_1 and router_core_3 (which use area 0). This prevents core_2 from forming adjacencies with the other cores and from participating in the backbone.\\n\\n- Routing tables:\\n  - router_dist_1_1: Has OSPF route to 10.200.0.0/24 via core_1 (OK).\\n  - router_core_1 and router_core_3: Have routes to 10.200.0.0/24 via server_access_router and to the 10.1.1.0/24 domain (OK).\\n  - router_core_2: Does not have a route to 10.200.0.0/24; only learns 10.2.1.0/24 via dist_2_1 (isolated).\\n  - router_dist_2_1: Does not have a route to 10.200.0.0/24; only shows 10.2.1.0/24 and 172.16.0.8/31 connected. Ping from router_dist_2_1 to dns_server fails with “Network is unreachable.”\\n  - Conclusion: The 10.2.1.0/24 domain is cut off from the server farm (10.200.0.0/24) because routes to the server network do not reach router_dist_2_1 through router_core_2.\\n\\n3) Impact on DHCP\\n- Hosts rely on DHCP via relay on the distribution routers to dhcp_server (10.200.0.8).\\n- Because router_dist_2_1 lacks reachability to 10.200.0.0/24 (and hence to the DHCP server), DHCP requests from host_2_1_1_1 cannot be relayed to or answered by the DHCP server.\\n- This directly explains host_2_1_1_1 having no IP address.\\n\\nAnomalies Identified\\n- Host 10.2.1.0/24 domain: No IP via DHCP on host_2_1_1_1; no routing from router_dist_2_1 to 10.200.0.0/24; ping attempts from router_dist_2_1 to server-side resources are unreachable.\\n- OSPF backbone break: router_core_2 not peering with core_1/core_3 due to area mismatch (area 66 on core links), isolating area 1 behind core_2 from area 0 and the server farm.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Primary faulty device: router_core_2 (OSPF configuration error on core-facing links).\\n- Affected downstream device: router_dist_2_1 (lacks routes to server farm due to upstream OSPF issue).\\n- Collateral effect: host_2_1_1_1 (10.2.1.0/24) cannot obtain DHCP lease or reach any server.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Misconfigured OSPF areas on router_core_2: core links (172.16.0.0/31 and 172.16.0.4/31) are placed in area 66 instead of area 0. This prevents backbone adjacency with router_core_1 and router_core_3 and blocks inter-area LSAs between area 1 (10.2.1.0/24) and the server area (10.200.0.0/24). As a direct consequence, DHCP relay from router_dist_2_1 to the central DHCP server fails, leaving host_2_1_1_1 without an IP.\\n\\nNormal/Healthy Components\\n- 10.1.1.0/24 access domain: DHCP working, reachability to DNS and web servers verified.\\n- OSPF on router_core_1, router_core_3, router_dist_1_1, and server_access_router: Neighbor adjacencies and routes to server farm present.\\n- DNS server and server farm: Reachable and responsive from 10.1.1.0/24; load balancer (web99.local) responds normally.\\n\\nNo remediation is proposed at this stage per the request., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='abe48828-82fb-4c85-b1be-98b6a32f91e2'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
